-- MOVES-Cavendish names partner and three new executives
-- 
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 12:20PM EDT
-- None



Oct 7 (Reuters) - UK-based advisory firm Cavendish Corporate Finance LLP promoted Anya Cummins to partner and appointed three new executives.

Cummins, who joined Cavendish in 2011, was previously a director at the firm. The firm, which specializes in sell side M&A, appointed Parit Patel, Duncan McKinlay and Marco Zamblera as corporate finance executives. Parit joins Cavendish's financial services team, led by partner Peter Gray, from the Financial Institutions Group at Cannacord Genuity, where he worked as an investment banking analyst on M&A transactions. McKinlay previously worked at Air New Zealand and advised SMEs.